## ğŸ“¦ What is `tar`?
- `tar` (tape archive) is used to **collect multiple files/directories into one file**.
- It does **not compress** the files â€” it simply bundles them together like a `.zip` in Windows **without reducing size**.
- Syntax:  
  ```bash
  tar [options] archive_name.tar files_or_dirs
âœ… Common tar options:
c â€“ Create archive

v â€“ Verbose (show progress)

f â€“ Specify filename of the archive

x â€“ Extract archive

t â€“ List contents inside archive

ğŸ§ª Create a .tar file
ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’» Example: Tar your current directory
bash
Copy
Edit
